Commentary: Roach is on target straight away. A little bit of moment. He bowls it on a length on the off pole line, it comes in a bit and Burns defends it to feel the ball on bat.
Good length delivery outside off this time by Roach. No swing on this one and Burns leave it alone.
Full and on middle and off, Burns defends it towards mid on.

NOT OUT! It is clipping the off pole but not enough to overturn the decision. Good length delivery outside off, Burns misreads it as the ball nips back in. Burns shoulders arms to it and the ball hits him high on his pads. Roach appeals but Dowrich behind the stumps is not as excited. Holder after a brief thought signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and it shows the ball was clipping the stumps. Umpire's call and Burns survives a huge scare. West Indies do not lose a review. They have all three of their reviews intact. Not surprising to see Burns misread one because it has been a long break and a little bit of rustiness can be expected especially in the early stages.
Outside off and Burns leaves it alone. This time no risk.
Full and on the stumps, Burns defends it to get through the over. Maiden from Roach. Tidy start from him.
Gabriel starts with a length ball down the leg side, Sibley watches it carefully and leaves the ball alone.
Another length ball on the pads, Sibley decides to leave the ball alone but gets hit on the thigh pad and the ball rolls to the leg side.

BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Gabriel! Just where he wants to be! Good length ball outside off, Sibley looks to defend without moving his feet but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and goes into the mitts of the keeper.

OUT! TIMBER! What a delivery from Shannon Gabriel! Just brilliant from the pacer! Sibley had no clue! Gabriel bowls this on a length outside off, Sibley looks to leave but the ball swings in sharply and goes on to hit the top of off stump. This is why West Indies' pacers are a force to reckon with. Burns was lucky to survive his rustiness but lady luck does not smile brightly on Sibley as his error in judgement has ended his innings. First international wicket after more than 110 days. A moment Gabriel and many will remember but Sibley would like to forget. He walks back for a duck. Terrific start for West Indies.
Short of a length ball outside off, Denly watches the ball carefully and leaves the ball alone.
Shortish in length, Denly hops and defends it to the point region. A wicket maiden!
Length ball outside the off stump line, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, with some swing away from the batsman, Burns pushes it to the point fielder.
Full delivery on middle, Rory comes forward and defends it to the off side.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Rory blocks it solidly off the back foot towards point.
Full delivery on the pads, Burns looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to the fine leg region and the batters manage to take a leg bye.
Good length ball outside off, tailing in sharply, Denly watches the ball carefully and leaves the ball alone.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Burns flicks it to square leg and calls Denly for a single.

Risky but just short of the mid on fielder! Short ball outside off, Denly looks to pull but does not get hold of it as well as he would have liked. Luckily for him, it falls just short of the fielder at mid on.
Length ball on middle, Denly blocks it to the mid off fielder.

That was close! Gabriel is having a wonderful time out there! He pitches it on a length outside off, which swings in sharply. Denly chooses to leave the ball but it passes just wide of the off stump and into the keeper's gloves.
Fullish delivery on middle, Joe pushes it to mid on.
Edgy! Good length ball on off, Denly looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and goes towards deep square leg. A single taken.
On a length on middle, Denly defends it out off the back foot.
Roach starts with a full delivery outside the off stump line, Denly lets the ball go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling from Kemar Roach! Good length ball outside off, Denly looks to push at it without moving his feet and he misses.
Length ball outside off, Denly leaves the ball alone.
On a length on off, Denly prods forward and defends it out to the off side.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length delivery from Gabriel! Burns stands tall and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Short of a length delivery outside off, Burns first looks to defend this one but decides to let it go to the keeper.
Full on the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.

FOUR! First boundary after ages! Poor delivery from Gabriel though and it had to be put away! Fullish on the pads, Burns missed out on the previous one but makes use of this one as he flicks it to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Rory leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside the off stump line, Denly shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on middle, Denly looks to defend but gets hit on the pads as the ball tails in after pitching.
Outside off, left alone.
Short ball on middle, Denly rocks on his back foot and then defends it out.
Length delivery outside the off stump line, Joe leaves the ball alone.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling! Good length delivery outside off, Denly looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
On off, defended off the front foot.
Back of a length delivery on middle and leg, Burns flicks it to square leg.
Good length ball on middle, Burns flicks it to the leg side and takes a single.
BOUNCER! Gabriel dishes this one around middle, Denly does well to duck under it.
Another short one from Gabriel which is bowled on middle, Denly ducks under it again.
FOUR! Poor ball and it has been duly put away! Short and wide outside off, from Gabriel, Denly slashes it through the point region for his first boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Burns flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Rory prods forward and blocks it to mid off.
Good length ball outside the off stump line, Burns leaves the ball alone.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Rory shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery outside off, angling away, Burns lets this ball go to the keeper.
Length ball on off, Burns solidly defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, which kicked off the surface after pitching. Denly looks to defend but the ball hits the upper part of the bat and rolls to the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, tailing in, Denly leaves the ball alone.

FOUR! Hammers the pull this time around! Denly tried this earlier as well but did not time it well but he has got a hold of this one. Short delivery on off, Joe pulls it past the mid on fielder and into the long on fence.
EDGED AND FOUR! Bit loose from Denly this time! Length ball outside off, Joe looks to drive but the ball takes the outside edge and goes past the slip cordon for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Denly leaves the ball alone.
Length ball on off, Joe defends it to the cover region.
Fullish delivery way outside off, Burns has no problems in leaving this one alone.
Good length ball outside off, Burns leaves this ball alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length delivery down the leg side, Rory shoulders arms.
Length ball on middle, Burns flicks it to square leg for a single.
Full on off, swinging in, Denly though defends it solidly back to the bowler.
FOUR! Poor start from Joseph! A gentle loosener! Back of a length delivery on the pads, Burns will pounce on that all day long as he flicks this to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Full on middle, Burns whips it to the leg side.
Short delivery on middle, Burns flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Burns defends it to point.
Good length ball outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Good shot! Full delivery outside off, Burns takes a stride forward and then drives it through the cover region. They pick up three before the fielder can chase after it and clean it up.
NO BALL! Holder starts with a short ball on middle, Burns works it to square leg for a single. Holder has overstepped and a no ball has been signaled.
Good length ball outside off, Denly defends it to the off side.
Length ball on middle, bouncing a little more than expected, Denly attempts to defend but gets hit on the gloves.
Good length ball outside off, Joe leaves the ball alone.
Length ball on middle, Denly defends it out.
Full on middle, Joe blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Denly leaves the ball alone.
FOUR! Cut away and cut away fine. Burns plays this shot really well. Slightly shorter outside off, Burns gets on his back foot and slashes it through point for a boundary.
Follows the boundary with a calm leave to the ball outside off.
Fuller and closer to the off pole, Burns gets behind it and blocks it.
Joseph hits the deck hard and tempts Burns to go after this ball outside off but Rory is in no mood to fall into this trap.
Full on the stumps, Burns defends it towards mid off.
Good length ball on off, Rory blocks it to get through the over.
EDGY! Good length ball on off, Denly looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes on the bounce to the second slip fielder.
Length ball on middle, Joe defends it solidly back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on off, Denly blocks it to the off side.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside the off stump line, Denly leaves the ball alone.
Full on off, Denly drives it to mid off for nothing.
Good length ball on off, Burns defends it to point.
Length ball outside off, Rory shoulders arms to this one.
Fullish delivery outside the off stump line, Rory lets this go to the keeper.
Length ball on middle, Burns watches it carefully and defends it out.
Another length ball outside off, Burns leaves this ball alone.
Fullish delivery on middle, Burns defends this out to the off side. Plays out a maiden and remains on 999 Test runs!

BEATEN! Excellent stuff from Holder! Would have loved to see it taking an edge though! Good length delivery outside off, Denly looks to defend it off the back foot but misses as the keeper collects it.
Full on middle, Joe flicks it to wide mid on for a single.
Fullish delivery outside the off stump line, Burns shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Burns makes another leave to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Burns looks to leave the ball but it touches the toe end of the bat and goes to slip cordon on the bounce.
Outside off, Burns carefully lets this go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Denly flicks it to mid on.
Short ball on middle, Denly looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the hips.
Good length ball on middle, Denly defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Denly looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Would have been close if not for that inside edge!
Joseph starts the day with a full delivery on the pads with no swing, Denly whips it to mid-wicket to see off the first delivery of Day 2.
BOUNCER! It is a good one at that! Joseph dishes this one around middle, Denly sways away from it.
Holder strays on his line first up as he pitches this one up down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Burns lets the ball go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rory defends it solidly off the back foot.
Holder pitches this on a length around the off stump line, Burns blocks it to the point region.
Full delivery on middle, Burns pushes it to the mid off region.
Good length ball on middle, Burns flicks it to square leg and takes a single. With that, Rory reaches 1000 runs in Test match cricket.
EDGY FOUR! Good length ball on off, Burns looks to push off the back foot but it takes the leading edge and goes to the deep point region for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Burns blocks it towards the mid off region.
Length ball outside off, Burns leaves the ball alone.
NO BALL! Gabriel oversteps! Short ball down the leg side, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on middle, Burns whips it to the leg side.
Good length delivery on off, Burns pushes it to cover.
Gabriel bowls this back of a length outside off, Burns sways away from it.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Denly looks to flick but the ball nips in sharply and it goes on to hit the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Length ball outside off, tailing in, Joe watches the ball carefully and leaves the ball alone.
Fullish delivery outside the off stump line, Denly shoulders arms to it.
Another length ball outside off, Denly lets the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, Denly makes another leave.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Denly defends it solidly off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Burns goes on his front foot and pushes this to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Burns watches it and then decides to leave it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Burns looks to flick but it takes the inside edge and it goes towards the deep square leg region. A couple taken.
Length ball on middle, Burns attempts to defend the ball from within the crease but he misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fullish delivery on middle, Burns plays it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Burns looks to defend but gets squared up. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through the cover region for a single.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Burns defends it off the back foot to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Burns drives it back to Holder.
Good length ball on off, Burns defends it off the back foot.
Full on off, Rory drives it to mid off from the front foot.
Another length ball on middle, with a little shape on it, Burns flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, Burns drives it crisply back towards the bowler but Holder manages to hold onto it.

FOUR! Flicked away nicely! Full delivery on middle, Denly flicks it uppishly towards the deep mid-wicket region. Brooks chases after it from mid-wicket but fails to do so as the ball touches the ropes.

OUT! TIMBER! Perfect delivery from Shannon Gabriel! He was the best bowler for the Windies on Day 1 and has started off in the same manner today as well. Just terrific stuff. Denly, as has been the case throughout his career so far. Gets off to a start and then fails to make it count. Excellent delivery from Gabriel. It is pacy and pitches outside off, this one nips back in sharply. Denly looks to defend but the ball goes right between the gate of the bat and pad to disturb the stumps. Fast bowler's delight and second wicket for Gabriel. He has looked excellent so far in this Test.
Good length ball down the leg side, Crawley looks to flick but misses. Dowrich moves to his right and saves it.
Gabriel bowls a bouncer on middle, Crawley lets the ball go to the keeper.
LEG BYE! Good length ball on the pads, Zak looks to flick but it brushes his thigh pad and rolls towards the fine leg region. A leg bye taken.
Length ball on off, Burns looks to push but it takes an outside edge and goes towards the gully fielder. An excellent over from Gabriel comes to an end.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley leaves the ball alone.
Length ball outside off, Zak watches it carefully and shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery on off, Crawley pushes it to the mid off region.
On a length on middle, Crawley flicks it to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
Excellent delivery! Roach bowls this on a length outside off, Crawley looks to flick but misses. He gets wrapped on the pads. An appeal is made but nothing from the umpire.
Good length ball outside off, Burns leaves the ball alone.
Fullish delivery outside off stump, Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Burns drives it through mid off and picks up a couple before the fielder can cut it off.

OUT! LBW! Brilliant decision to review from West Indies. Holder was not convinced for the review but Gabriel convinces him and it has worked wonders. Very full delivery on middle, and leg, Burns moves towards the off side to flick but misses. He gets rapped on the pads and there is a huge appeal made for LBW. The umpire shakes his head. Holder goes for the review after Gabriel convinces him to do so and the Ultra Edge shows that there is no bat. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows all three reds. Burns has to go and yet another case of an England batsman getting a start and then throwing it away. West Indies have been brilliant in the morning.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Stokes looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal is made for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
WIDE! Outside off, left alone by Stokes. Wide signaled.
Length ball on off, Ben defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery outside off, tempting Crawley to go for the drive but he leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Zak once again shoulders arms to it.
Roach continues bowling the fourth stump line but Crawley is not interested in disturbing it.
Full and closer to the off pole, Crawley gets behind it and blocks it.
FOUR! Beautiful shot to get off the mark! Roach is guilty of overpitching it around off, Crawley shows amazing footwork and leans on his drive through covers for a boundary.
Roach pulls back his length and bowls this on a good length area. It is on off, Crawley defends it towards mid on and gets through the over.
Good length ball around off, Stokes looks to leave but it hits the bottom half of the bat and rolls to the slip cordon.
On a length on middle, Stokes looks to defend but it hits the inside edge onto the pitch. Excellent stuff from Shannon Gabriel.
Full delivery on off, Ben takes a full stride forward and defends it towards the cover region.
Full on off, Stokes pushes it to the cover region.
FOUR! Gets off the mark in style does Stokes! Short ball on middle, Stokes stands tall and then pulls it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Fullish delivery on middle, Stokes pushes it to the mid on region.
Good length ball on the pads, Crawley flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Stokes defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball around off, Stokes looks to defend but gets rapped on the pads. The Windies' players put up an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Good decision not to review as the impact was outside off.
Outside off, Ben lets the ball go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball outside off, Crawley leaves the ball alone.
Length ball outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to it.
Another length ball outside off, Stokes has no problems in leaving it alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes does not bother playing at that one.
Good length ball on off, Stokes moves to the off side and defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Stokes looks to defend but it whizzes past the bat and Dowrich's gloves.
Roach dishes a full delivery on middle, Zak prods forward and defends it to the off side.
Fullish on off, Crawley pushes it to cover and takes a quick single.
Full delivery outside off, Stokes lets the ball through to the keeper.
On a length on off, Stokes takes a few steps forward and then defends it to mid on.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes leaves the ball alone.
Lovely delivery from Roach! Full delivery outside off, Stokes moves a little forward to counter the swing but the ball whizzes past the outside edge, into the keeper's gloves.
Good length ball on off, Crawley defends it back to the bowler.
Length delivery outside off, Zak shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length delivery on off, Crawley defends it to the slip cordon.
Full delivery on off, Crawley prods forward and pushes it to point.
Just short! Good length ball outside off, Zak looks to defend but takes the bottom hand off the bat. It takes the outside edge but luckily for Crawley, it lands short of the second slip fielder.
EDGY FOUR! Lucky! Full delivery on middle, Crawley looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes lets the ball go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Excellent from Roach! Good length delivery outside off, moving away, Stokes looks to defend but misses it altogether.
FOUR! Lovely, lovely shot from Stokes! Good length delivery around off, Stokes moves towards the off side and then drives it through the mid on region for a boundary.
On middle, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, Ben does bother to play at that one.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes walks across and then decides to leave it alone.

OUT! LBW! That looked so, so out to the naked eye! Another review which goes in the favour of West Indies. Jason Holder is having a field day with his reviews. Brilliant stuff from the Windies. Zak Crawley does not make use of the opportunity given to him in the absence of Joe Root. Another batsman succumbs to the movement of the ball with his own feet not moving. Full delivery around off, which swings in sharply. Crawley looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Holder and the rest appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Kettleborough gets across sideways to see where the ball has ended up, does an 'ooo' with his mouth but shakes his head. Holder is confident and goes for the review. Before the Ultra Edge rolls in, initially there is some confusion. Has the ball deflected off the bat? Nope. No deviation or spike on the Ultra Edge. The Ball Tracker shows all reds and Zak has to go. England are in deep trouble in their first innings and need their captain Ben Stokes to step up. But the question is - how will he play now? Take your side till Lunch without any more wickets or counter-attack?
Good length ball on off, Pope defends it out.
Length ball on off, Pope pushes it to cover and gets off the mark with a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Stokes pushes it to gully.
Full on middle, Pope flicks it wide of mid on where Gabriel dives and makes a good stop. Keeps it to a single.
On off, defended solidly by Stokes.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Stokes defends it out.
Good length ball on off, Stokes rushes forward and then defends it back to the bowler.
Very full delivery outside off, tempting Stokes to go after it but Ben leaves it alone.
Holder dishes a length ball outside the off stump line, Pope leaves the ball alone.
Length ball on middle, Pope defends it towards mid on.
On a length on middle, Pope plays it back to the bowler.
Fullish delivery outside the off stump line, Pope lets the ball go to the keeper.
FOUR! Well played from Pope! Nice way to get your first boundary in the innings! Good length ball on middle, Pope flicks it nonchalantly through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.

FOUR! This is even better! Probably the shot of the day! Another length ball from Holder and bowls it outside off, Pope takes a stride forward and drives it crisply through the cover region for a boundary.
Joseph starts with a full delivery on off, Stokes drives it to the mid off fielder.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.
Fuller on off, Stokes defends it with a dead bat.
FOUR! Glorious from the skipper. Not a very bad ball from Joseph, it is just class of Ben Stokes. Full on off, Stokes just waits for it and helps it right off the meat through mid off for a boundary.
Joseph pulls his length back and bowls it slightly short around off, Stokes looks to pull but it comes off the bottom of his bat and goes towards mid-wicket.
On off, Stokes pushes it towards mid off and gets though the over. 4 from it.
Good length ball on middle, Pope looks to flick but gets an inside edge towards mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Pope glances it wide of mid-wicket for a couple.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Aussie fans, Aussie fans, where art thou? Ahhh... they must be booing the English from home. 87 is considered as an unlucky number for Australia but in the recent past, it has been England who have been facing more bad luck at that number in cricket. 5 down and still a quarter of an hour to go to Lunch. England are in tatters here. If Holder was looking rusty on Day 1, he has been the complete opposite bowler today! This bloke was looking so good - Ollie Pope. But that is what happens when you get some confidence. You don't quite want to let balls go, which you should, more often than not in a Test inning. That too, when you have faced just a dozen balls. Pope sees this length delivery around off and thinks, 'Well, let me just nurdle it around the corner for one.' What happens instead is the ball moves away, takes the outside edge as Pope looks to control the damage after realising the late movement but is too late. Outside edge to Dowrich and West Indies get another one. Shake of the head from Pope but mate, this is one ball which you could have left alone.
Length ball outside the off stump line, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler defends it out.
Good length ball on off, Stokes defends it.
Length delivery on middle, Ben defends it to the on side and looks for a run but Buttler is quick to turn it down.
On off, Ben pushes it to mid off.
Length ball on off, Stokes is calm in his approach and has no problem blocking it.
On top of middle, Stokes defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball on the fourth stump line, Stokes lets it carry to the keeper. Good over from Joseph, it's a maiden.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler lets the ball through to the keeper.
Buttler is off the mark! Good length ball on middle, Jos flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length outside off, Stokes leaves the ball alone.
Good length ball again from Holder, Stokes blocks it solidly to the off side.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes flicks it to deep square leg and takes a single. They think of a second but decide against it.
Length ball on off, Buttler defends it off the back foot to the point region.
Good length ball on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot towards mid off.

DROPPED! Tough chance! The plan of bowling short to Ben Stokes almost worked! Excellent captaincy from Holder but at this level, this catch should have been taken. Joseph dishes this short around middle which bounces a little more than expected, Stokes does not hold back and goes for it as he looks to smash it into orbit. He attempts the pull as it takes the top edge and goes towards backward square leg. Roach runs in from fine leg and manages to reach it. He dives forward but fails to hold onto it. The ball pops out of his hands and enables Stokes to take two. Ben Stokes is an excellent player and dropping him can prove costly. Will it be so?
LEG BYES! Short ball around the leg stump line, Stokes looks to duck but gets hit on the elbow. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters take a couple.
On a length on middle, Stokes defends it out.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
FOUR! This time Stokes gets a hold of it well! Short delivery which does not rise high enough! Stokes waits for it and then pulls it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.

Ohh! Holder is bowling really well here. Good length delivery on off, it nips back in. Buttler looks to defend but misreads the swing on this one. Luckily for him the ball goes towards backward square leg off the inner half of his bat allowing him to take two as the fielder from fine leg cleans it up.
On the pads, Buttler turns it towards fine leg and eases to the other end.
Fuller around off, Stokes defends it from right under his eyes.
Good length ball outside off, asking Stokes to go for the drive but he shows respect to this delivery and lets it carry to the keeper.
Outside off, Stokes is aware of his off stump and shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Stokes has nothing to do with it.

FOUR! Nicely played from Jos Buttler! Shortish in length outside off, Buttler stands tall and just pushes it towards the deep cover region for a boundary. The fielder chases after it from cover but fails to get there in time.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Full delivery on middle, Buttler looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but a shake of the head from the umpire. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it was going to be missing the leg stump.
On off, pushed to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler leaves the ball alone.
On a length on off, Jos looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and goes towards deep square leg. A single taken.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single. LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Gabriel starts the post-Lunch session with a good length ball outside off, with no swing. Stokes watches the ball carefully and lets the ball go to the keeper.
This time, Gabriel goes full on middle, Stokes pushes this comfortably towards mid on for a dot.

FOUR! Poor bowling from Gabriel and a nice way to start the session from Stokes! Short and wide from Shannon and Stokes is quick to pounce on it as he punches it through the cover region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes flicks it to square leg and gives Jos Buttler the strike.
Good length ball around the off stump line, Buttler looks to push it off the back foot but it takes the inside edge and goes towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Not a great start to the afternoon session from Gabriel! He was excellent in the morning one but has strayed a bit in the first over of the new session . Short outside off, Buttler sees the room to free his arms and just slashes it over point for a boundary. Jos has been struggling with the bat in the longer formats, this will do a world of good to his confidence. 9 from the first over post the Lunch session.
On a good length on middle, Stokes flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery just outside off, Stokes lets it go.
Full delivery on middle, Stokes takes a few steps forward and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off, Stokes blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Ben flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length and outside off, Buttler does not bother to play at that.
FOUR! Effortless from Buttler! Slightly shorter delivery around off, Buttler is quick to transfer the weight to his back foot and punches it through covers with minimum of fuss for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Buttler defends it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery outside off, Buttler lets it go.
On a good length on off, Jos defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Stokes drives it towards mid on.

Length delivery on the pads, Stokes looks to flick but gets it off the thigh pad. It goes towards the keeper where Dowrich collects it safely. There is an appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire.
Outside off, Stokes offers no shot to this one.

FOUR! Exquisite from the England skipper! He is looking good out there and that dropped catch before Lunch is starting to haunt West Indies a little bit! Full delivery on middle, Stokes flicks it with ease towards the deep mid-wicket boundary.
On a length on middle, Stokes flicks it towards fine leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.

DROPPED! Straight in, straight out! Boy, Stokes gets another life. This was a sitter and West Indies are letting themselves down. Full and outside off, right in the slot to drive and the big Ben does. But he cannot keep it down. The ball goes straight but low to Shamarh Brooks at short extra cover who gets down but spills it! Shake of the head from Holder. You drop someone once, it is a mistake. But you do it again, it is a crime!
Gabriel bowls a bouncer, Buttler ducks under it.
On a good length on off, Buttler keeps it out.
Good length ball on off, Buttler defends it to covers.
Good length delivery on middle, Buttler looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! Caught behind! The West Indies skipper gets the better of the English skipper. A good innings from Stokes comes to an end and the budding partnership has been broken. Roach and Brooks will be relieved as their dropped catches has not cost West Indies a lot. Excellent delivery from Holder. He comes around the wicket and bowls it full around off, Stokes looks to work it to the leg side but the ball comes in and straightens enough to kiss the outside edge and go straight into the mitts of Shane Dowrich behind the stumps. He makes no mistake and the West Indies players are ecstatic. They are in command of this game and are into the bowlers now.

OUT! LBW! Another review taken by Holder, another decision has been overturned! Boy, Holder has been terrific today. Everything he has touched has turned to gold, be it with the ball in hand or his reviews, he's been spot on. He thinks for a review and after consulting his teammates, Jason opts for the review. The Ultra Edge shows that there is no bat on it. What about Ball Tracker? It shows all reds and Holder has got his 5th wicket. England are just 2 wickets away from being bowled out.

But this partnership helped England reach over 200. ENGLAND HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 204.

The Ultra Edge shows no bat but the Ball Tracker shows that it is pitching outside leg and Campbell survives. Excellent decision to review and West Indies' streak of successful reviews continues.

He has been troubling Campbell the whole innings so far and he has finally been rewarded. Good length ball on middle, Campbell looks to defend but gets rapped on the pads. England appeal and once again the on-field umpire raises the finger. Campbell goes for the review yet again but this time he is not so lucky as the Ultra Edge shows that there is no bat on it. The Ball Tracker then rolls in and it shows all reds. Campbell has to go now and the streak of West Indies' successful reviews is over.

NOT OUT! It has touched the back pad. Excellent start from James Anderson on Day 3. Just where he would like to be first up. He bowls it on a length around off, Brathwaite looks to defend but the ball goes in between his bat and pad towards Buttler. There was a noise as the ball passed the bat and England appeal. The umpire shakes his head. England after some thought opt for the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is no bat on it. In fact, it has touched the back pad before going through to the keeper. Contrasting luck for both the skippers so far with the DRS. Holder was spot on with his but Stokes has taken one and a poor one to be honest. The hosts lose their first review out of three. Anderson though will be happy with the line and the hint of moment on this one and would like to hit it there consistently.

It has been an excellent partnership and are keeping West Indies in control here. Can they continue on from here?

NO BALL! Ohh, Jofra Archer! What have you done? A decision which goes your way and then you commit a crime of bowling a no ball. It seems like the sun is shining on the Windies. Good length ball on off and middle, Hope looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. England and the rest appeal and the umpire obliges as he raises the finger. Hope discusses with Brathwaite and goes for the review at the last moment. And what does the replays how? It shows that Archer has overstepped. Hope will look to make use of this opportunity. He would have been out if it was not for a no ball as the Ball Tracker shows that it was umpire's call.
Short ball around middle, Hope ducks under it.
Another short one on middle, Shai hops and defends it towards the off side.
Jofra dishes a short one down the leg side, Hope lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Tossed up delivery on off, Brathwaite defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Brathwaite plays it towards third man for a single.

OUT! Caught! Sharp catch by captain Ben Stokes. Good bowling by Bess. He gives this one air and bowls it outside off, tempting Hope to drive. Hope obliges and expects the ball to spin in but this one keeps straight and takes a thick outside edge which goes to the right of first slip. Stokes has a great pair of hands and makes a sharp catch look rather easy. England needed a wicket and they have got it. West Indies still in command though. England need to find a way to get wickets and build on this momentum.

Fifty for Kraigg Brathwaite! He has played a very good innings here and after a superb bowling performance from his teammates, he has not let it go and has kept West Indies' nose ahead. He knows the job is not done and he will look to make this count and convert this into a hundred. He gets to his 18th fifty by stroking this short ball from Bess towards point for a single. No crowd to applaud his effort in the stadium but all the West Indies' fans will be happy with it, that's for sure.

OUT! LBW! Stokes has the last laugh and the expensive over has ended on a fruitful note. End of a very good innings from Kraigg Brathwaite but he will be disappointed not to convert this into a century. Stokes dishes out a good length delivery on off which nips back in. Brathwaite looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. England appeal and after a thought, the on-field umpire raises his finger. Brathwaite has a  chat with Brooks and at the eleventh hour signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and Stokes, unlike Archer, has not overstepped his line. The Ultra Edge then rolls in and it shows that there is no bat involved. The Ball Tracker comes up and shows that it is umpire's call on impact as well on hitting the stumps. Game of margins this and West Indies won't lose their review but they will lose their man.

OUT! CAUGHT! There is a clear spike on Ultra Edge and Brooks has to depart after looking so good. What a waste of a review though! Anderson has been exceptional since the Lunch break and has been rewarded with a wicket. Good length ball outside off, Brooks looks to defend without moving his feet and ends up edging it behind. Buttler takes it comfortably and all of England players appeal. The umpire raises his dreaded finger after giving it a thought. Surprisingly, Brooks consults his partner who convinces him to go for a review. Anderson's front foot is fine and Ultra Edge shows that there is a spike on it as the ball passes the bat. Brooks has to go and he takes the review with him as well. England needed this wicket as West Indies are inching closer to wiping off the deficit.

He still goes for the lofted shot but does not get the required elevation and the ball goes straight to James Anderson at mid off who takes it with no fuss. The English players are happy and why wouldn't they be!

OUT! LBW! Another on-field call that has been overturned. Chase's patient and very good innings comes to an end. England desperately needed a wicket and they have got it. Once again it is Anderson who has done the damage. He has been the best bowler for England and Stokes so far. Anderson bowls a good length delivery on off, it is bowled at a good pace and nips back in. Chase looks to defend but misses and gets hit around the knee roll of his front pad. The England players put in an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Anderson, Stokes and Buttler all have a quick chat after which Stokes signals the 'T'. Anderson's foot is fine so we move onto Ultra Edge and there is no spike there. Is height going to be an issue? No, it's not as Ball Tracker comes in and shows all reds as the ball is going on to hit the middle and leg pole. Chase's vigilant knock comes to an end and England get the wicket they were craving for. End of an excellent partnership as well which has taken West Indies in the driver's seat. They lead by 63 runs.

Good length ball on middle, Denly looks to flick off the back foot but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Full delivery on off, Denly drives it through the mid off region and picks up three before Chase runs from mid off and cuts it off.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Sibley ducks under it.
Fullish delivery on middle, Sibley plays it towards mid on and takes off for a single. The fielder runs in and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Would have been close had he hit.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to the leg side.
Length ball on off, Sibley is solid in defense as he blocks it to cover.
Full on middle, Sibley pushes it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling from Roach! Length ball outside off, Sibley looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to mid on and takes a single.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Denly.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sibley plays it back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Dom tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely guided away! Shortish delivery around off, Sibley camps on his back foot and guides it to the third man region for a boundary.
This time Joseph goes full around off, Sibley prods forward and blocks it to mid off.
Full on middle, Sibley pushes it back to the bowler.
Short ball around the off stump line, Dom sways away from it.
Roach dishes a good length ball on middle, Denly blocks it back to Roach.
Length ball on off, Denly defends it to point and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Good length delivery outside off, left alone.

EDGED! Length ball on off, Denly looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards second slip where the fielder misfields. It travels towards third man and the batters take a couple. The fielder throws a direct hit at the keeper's end but Denly was in.

Good length ball on middle and leg, Denly looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal is made for LBW but the umpire turns it down. The Ball Tracker shows that it is going over the stumps.
Length ball on middle, Joe defends it out.
Gabriel starts with a length ball outside the off stump line, Sibley has no problems in leaving this one alone.
On a length on middle, Dom works it to mid-wicket for a dot.
Very full delivery outside off, Sibley digs it through the gully region and picks up three before the fielder chases and cleans it up before it reaches the ropes.
Fullish delivery outside off, Denly makes a leave to this one.
Short ball around middle, Denly ducks under it.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Denly shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Good bowling by Roach! Good length ball outside off, Sibley looks to defend but misses it altogether.
On a length outside off, Dom shoulders arms to it.
On a length on off, Sibley plays it to gully.
Full delivery on middle, Dom defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, defended out onto the pitch.
Good length ball on off, Sibley defends it to the cover region.
On a length on off, Denly defends it to cover.
Length ball on middle, Joe blocks it out off the back foot back to the bowler.
EDGY! Lucky for Denly! Short ball outside off, Denly looks to cut without moving his feet but gets an inside edge which goes past the stumps towards fine leg. A couple taken.
Full delivery on middle, pushed to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Joe flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Good length delivery on middle, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Holder starts with a full delivery on off, Denly pushes it to mid off. He wants a single but is denied.
Length ball on off, Denly takes a stride forward and drives it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Denly decides to leave this ball alone.
Good length ball on off, nipping back in, Denly looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fullish delivery outside off, Joe lets the ball go to the keeper.
Holder bowls a length ball on off, Denly prods forward and defends it to cover.
Full delivery outside off, angling in sharply, Sibley leaves it alone.
Full delivery outside off, Dom drives it through the cover region and picks up a couple. 100 up for England.
Fullish on middle, Sibley drives it straight back and hits the stumps at the bowler's end. The ball rolls to mid-wicket, allowing the batters to take a single.
Another full delivery on off, Denly looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes towards point where the fielder makes a half stop. A single taken.
Good length ball down the leg side, Sibley looks to flick but misses.
Good length delivery on middle, Sibley works it to deep mid-wicket and picks up three to keep the strike for the next over.
Good length delivery on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, Sibley pushes it to mid on and takes a single.
Full delivery outside off, Joe drives but finds the cover fielder.
Good length ball on off, Denly gets behind the ball and defends it out.
FOUR! Shot of the day! You can watch this shot all day long! Full of class! Full delivery on middle, Denly drives it past the bowler and into the fence.
Denly follows the boundary with a defense to this good length ball on off to cover.

FIFTY! 1st Test fifty for Dom Sibley! He got a century the last time he crossed a fifty! This has been a brilliant innings. He is keeping England in the game. Good length ball on middle, Sibley flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple. Can he continue on to score a century?

NO BALL! Sibley is riding his luck! No crime is worse in cricket when you get a batsman dismissed but it ends up as a No Ball. That's what Shannon Gabriel has done. This can prove very costly. Dom Sibley has to make sure that he makes full use of this. Short ball outside off, Sibley hops and looks to defend. It takes the inside edge and goes onto hit the off stump. Sibley is disappointed but he has been told to wait by the umpire. They want to check for the no ball. Replays roll in and they show that Gabriel's foot is on the line, nothing behind. Dom is lucky and now will hope to convert this start.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Sibley.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sibley does not make use of the opportunity he got earlier in the over. He has been strangled down the leg side before as well in his first-class and international career and West Indies have exploited it this time. A hundred was on the offing here and Sibley has thrown it away. He will be very disappointed with this but has to make the long walk back to the pavilion. Gabriel dishes out a good length ball down the leg side, Sibley cannot resist as he tries to flick this to fine leg but he can only get a faint edge to the keeper who dives to his left to take the catch. Gabriel takes a sigh of relief as that No Ball did not cost much and they have got rid of the set batsman. England trail by 1 run.
Good length ball on middle, Zak defends it out.
Full on middle, Crawley pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, defended out.
Holder bowls a bouncer, Denly does well to duck under it.
On a good length and outside off, Denly shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Denly flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off, Joe blocks it off the back foot.

NOT OUT! For, once, Holder's review goes to a waste in this Test match! It has gone off Denly's shoulder! Wonder what made him go for the review. Holder dishes out a short ball around off, Denly looks to pull but misses. He gets hit on the shoulder and it goes to second slip. West Indies appeal but it is turned down. Holder after some discussion with the umpire, takes the review. Holder is fine on the front foot but was very close to the line. The Ultra Edge rolls in and shows that there is no spike as the ball passed the bat and it has gone off the shoulder. The decision remains not out. Poor review from Holder this time.
FOUR! Nicely pulled away! Short ball on middle, Denly pulls it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.

Well fielded! Tossed up on off, Denly dances down and lifts it over the bowler's head. Brathwaite runs across from long on and makes a good stop. The umpires check whether it is a clean save and it is. Two taken.

Short ball around off, Crawley looks to pull but does not time it well and it goes towards the mid-wicket fielder. No run.
Good length ball outside off, Zak leaves the ball alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, Crawley punches it to the deep cover region for a couple. The fielder throws it to the bowler's end but the batsman is well in. 150 up. England lead by 37 runs.

Full delivery on middle, Crawley drives it straight back. Joseph tries to get a hand on it but misses and the ball goes on to hit the stumps at the bowler's end. Had Alzarri touched it, Denly would have been a goner.
Length ball on middle, Zak flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball on middle, Crawley looks to pull but gets hit on the body.

OUT! Caught! Another soft dismissal but Chase isn't complaining. Denly's curse of getting out between 11-30 continues. He will be fuming with himself. This is not a delivery he would have envisioned himself getting out to. Nothing delivery from Chase. It is a straighter delivery on the pads, Denly flicks it but does so uppishly, just to the left of Holder at mid-wicket. Denly once again gets the start and throws it away. The West Indies skipper makes no mistake and accepts it graciously. England once again lose a wicket against the run of play. 3 down with the lead of 37.

IN THE AIR BUT SAFE! What are you doing Crawley! Your side has just lost a wicket and you play that kind of shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Crawley looks to flick but gets a leading edge. Campbell runs after it but the ball is ahead of him. Two taken. Crawley will feel really lucky here.

Close! Floated ball on middle, Crawley comes down and flicks it to mid on and takes off for a single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses by a mile and the ball rolls towards third man. The batters take another run before the fielder cleans it up. Had the mid on fielder hit, it might have been close.
Floated on middle, Zak defends it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Excellent use of the feet! Tossed up ball outside off, Crawley puts on his dancing shoes and lifts it over the mid off fielder for a boundary.
Flatter one on middle, Zak pushes it to long on for a single.

NOT OUT! Another poor review in this innings from Jason Holder! His charm regarding reviews worked in the first innings but not in this one. Poor decision. Very full delivery around off, Stokes misses and it goes towards slip but the keeper and West Indies think that it has gone off the bat to the slip fielder. The umpire does not think so and shakes his head. Holder at the last moment goes for the review. Brathwaite is fine on his front foot but the Ultra Edge shows that there was a spike but that was of the bat hitting the ground. No spike as the ball passes the bat. Not out is the decision and Stokes survives. Another review wasted by West Indies. England lead by 54 runs.
Floated on middle, defended out to the off side.
Flighted ball outside off, Stokes looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.

BEATEN FIRST UP! Chase starts with a floated ball outside off, Crawley prods forward and looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.

FOUR! Stokes gets off the mark in some style. It took him 19 balls to do it. Full delivery on middle, Stokes drives it through the mid on region for a boundary.

Good length ball outside the off stump line, Stokes shoulders arms to it. 4 runs from the Holder over.

FIFTY! 2nd one for Crawley in Tests! Excellent innings from Zak Crawley! He has looked good and comfortable and will be itching to continue on. Unlike Denly, he has made use of the opportunity. Chase floats this up on middle, Crawley goes on his knees and then reverse sweeps it to the third man region for a boundary to get the milestone. Crawley has played spin really well and this ball was another instance of it.
On a good length on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Stokes is looking to attack the spinner and it has worked on this occasion. Loopy delivery on middle, Stokes goes on his knees and plays a slog sweep towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated delivery just outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
On middle, Stokes defends it off the back foot.

TOP EDGE BUT SAFE! Short delivery outside off, Stokes looks to pull but gets a top edge. Holder from the slip cordon chases after it but the ball falls just ahead of him. Two taken. Not the first time that Alzarri Joseph has troubled Stokes with the short ball in this Test.
Short delivery on middle, Stokes pulls it through mid-wicket. Two runs taken.

Floated delivery on off, Stokes punches it through point for a run. 50-run partnership comes up. These two have taken England out of troubled waters somewhat and are doing a terrific job so far. The job is not done yet and they will look to continue piling up runs.

OUT! CAUGHT! Holder gets Stokes again in this match. It has truly been the battle of the captains. Holder had him in the first innings while Stokes returned the favour when West Indies batted and now Holder does it once again. 2-1 in favour of Holder in this personal duel. Stokes dismissed in the 40s once more but he has taken England to a strong position. Holder bowls a good length delivery around middle, Stokes moves to the off side and then looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards Shai Hope who is standing a bit wide at third slip. Big wicket and West Indies have a hope of making it back in this game. 200 wickets for Holder in all formats. Will they be able to restrict the hosts' lead now?
Good length ball on middle, Pope defends this out.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Crawley's magnificent innings has come to an end. He will be disappointed as this has opened the doors for the visitors because of two successive wickets and has given them a chance to make a comeback in this game. Good length ball on middle, Crawley looks to flick but gets a leading edge back towards the bowler who makes no mistake. Zak walks back slowly to the pavilion. England lead by 139 runs.
FOUR! Off the mark with a boundary! Good length ball on off, Buttler guides it to the third man region for a boundary.

NOT OUT! Great review and another decision that has been overturned. Not the first one we have seen in this Test. Buttler survives a huge scare. Good length delivery pitching outside off from Holder. It comes back in sharply. Buttler looks to defend but the jag back is too good for him and he misses. The ball hits him on the front pad. Holder and his teammates go up in an appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Buttler has a quick word with his partner and signals the 'T' very quickly. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge first confirms no involvement of bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows that the ball was missing the leg pole. Buttler survives.
Length ball on off, Buttler blocks it succesfully this time.
Fuller on off, Buttler pushes it to cover.

FOUR! Beautiful! Buttler needs a few of these for his own confidence. A rare bad ball from Holder. He strays one on middle and leg, Buttler is quick to pick it and flicks it right off the middle through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On the pads, Buttler looks to turn it to the on side bus misses. The ball goes towards fine leg off his hips and he takes a leg bye.
On off, Pope blocks it to see off the over.

Alzarri Joseph has been brilliant in this spell and shows the world what he can do! He dishes out a good length delivery on off, nipping in, Buttler goes for the drive but does not move his feet at all. The ball takes the inside edge and uproots the leg stump. Buttler's tough run in Tests continues. England lead by 151 runs.

What about Ball Tracker? It is impact in line but umpire's call on hitting the stumps.

OUT! TIMBER! Gabriel has found some rhythm in this spell and has been rewarded with the wicket of Bess. Bess was looking comfortable but he has to go. Brilliant bowling from Gabriel. Gabriel and West Indies are in the middle of a good spell here and will hope to bowl England out early. The hosts lead by 164 runs.
Good length ball on off, Archer defends it to the off side.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! This is just excellent bowling! Gabriel is proving that he is a force to be reckoned with. He was in the reserves but was added just a few days before the squad was announced and he is delivering the goods. Short of a length delivery around off, Pope hops to defend this one but gets an inside edge onto the stumps. What a session this has been for West Indies. Pope is disgusted with himself as he was the last recognized batsman in and England would have wanted him to continue on for the side. England lead by 165 runs. How many more runs can the hosts add?
On a good length on off, Archer looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It lands safely towards gully.

The ball flies between gully and second slip. The fielder at gully dives to his left but the ball is too wide of him and goes to the third man fence for a boundary. These are valuable runs for England.

Gabriel comes in and hits the deck hard on top of middle and off, Wood goes on his back foot and looks to play it through point but ends up getting a thick outside edge which goes straight into the mitts of Dowrich. He takes a dolly and England have just one wicket in the kitty and they lead by 189.

More valuable runs for England!

Hopeful review from Archer but to no avail. England bowled out for 313. West Indies need 200 to win the game and take the lead in the series.

Brooks does not even bother to take it upstairs. Good decision that as the Ball Tracker later on shows that the ball was going to hit the middle stump. This has been an awful start from the West Indies. They are clearly on the back foot here.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a nasty delivery! England needed this wicket desperately as this partnership was taking the game away from them. What an excellent piece of bowling from Jofra Archer! He has been the best bowler so far in this innings. Jofra bends his back and bowls the effort ball and makes the ball shoot up off the surface. It is a well directed one as well. Chase looks to defend but the awkward height and the pace beats him and the ball kisses his thumb before lobbing off his shoulder to the keeper. Buttler jogs forward and takes a simple catch. Brilliant from Archer. This is why he is so highly rated. Nothing is happening off the surface but he has made it happen. West Indies still on top of this chase but can England make this opening count and make a comeback?

NOT OUT! Umpire's call on impact it is! Bess flights this one up on middle, Dowrich looks to flick but gets hit on the back pad. Bess and the rest appeal but nothing from the umpire. Bess is confident and convinces Stokes to go for the review. The Ultra Edge shows no bat while the Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on impact. England will not lose their review.

NOT OUT! It has gone off the shoulder! Excellent review from Dowrich. He was very confident and it has paid off. This is another excellent delivery from Archer. Short around middle, Dowrich hops and looks to defend but it seems to have gone off the bat and into the first slip's hands. England players are celebrating and the umpire raises his finger. Dowrich immediately reviews. This is an indication that he has not hit it. The Ultra Edge shows that it has hit the shoulder and not the bat. Brilliant stuff from Shane Dowrich.

OUT! CAUGHT! Is it? No, it is a NO BALL as Stokes has overstepped. England have not taken their chances and this is another of those instance. This would have got them back in the game but it was not to be. Good length ball from Stokes outside off, Dowrich goes for the drive but it takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip where Dom Sibley makes no mistake. The umpires check for the No Ball and the replays show that it is. Stokes knew it as he showed disappointment immediately after he bowled that ball.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time there is no doubt about the no ball and Dowrich's valuable innings comes to an end. He got lucky in the previous ball but not this time. Stokes is glad and so is the rest of the England team. They still have a chance to win this game. Length ball on off, moving away, Dowrich looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes to the right of the keeper. Buttler dives to that side and manages to take the catch. FOUR! Excellent control from Blacwood. Short ball outside off, Jermaine knows there is no third man so he lofts it over gully in a controlled manner and gets himself a boundary to move to 95 and 11 runs away from victory.

OUT! Caught! Stokes gets another one and is the English miracle still possible? Well there is a glimmer of hope for that to happen now. End of a fantastic innings from Blackwood. He will be gutted not to see off the game and also miss out on a well-deserved century. Stokes bowls a fuller delivery outside off, Jermaine looks to go over mid off. He does not get the desired elevation and ends up hitting it to the right of mid off. Anderson there swiftly moves on that side and takes a simple catch. Blackwood cannot finish it off but what a fantastic knock he has played. Will he be furious to miss out the chance to take his side over the line by himself? Yes absolutely but that does not take away anything from his stupendous knock.  Take a bow!
Appeal but turned down. Going down leg. On the pads, Campbell looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Stifled appeal from the hosts but the umpire turns it down.
Stokes hits the deck hard, Campbell gets on his back foot and blocks it to get through the over.
Good length ball on off, Holder defends it to point and takes a single. More 10 required.

BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Wood! Good length ball outside off, Campbell looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.

Again on the pads, Holder turns it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Good length delivery outside off, Campbell is in no hurry and is happy to watch it carry to the keeper.
Now a single. Fuller on off, Campbell pushes it to the right of mid off and takes a single. West Indies just a maximum away now.

Outside off, Campbell won't disturb that.

Ouch! That is a nasty blow. Wood bangs it in short and the ball comes in with the angle at a ferocious pace. Campbell looks to sway away but is too late. He manages to get his hand off but gets hit on the grill.
Good length ball outside off, Campbell punches it sweetly but straight to the man at point.

Full on off, Campbell hits it straight, Wood is unable to hold onto it. Campbell calls for a quick single, Holder is a bit late to respond but his long strides ensure he reaches the other end without any fuss.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Holder sways away from it.
Good length ball on off which comes in with the angle, Holder tucks it towards mid-wicket and looks for a single but Campbell is quick to refuse his skipper. Good call.
FOUR! Just a run away now. The scores are level. Short and wide outside off, Campbell is quick to pounce onto it and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.

That is it! West Indies win the game by 4 wickets and they have started the series in an emphatic fashion. Big win for Jason Holder and West Indies. Fantastic performance from the tourists. Stokes bowls on the pads, Campbell flicks it in front of square leg and takes a single to TAKE A 1-0 LEAD IN THE SERIES.
